Bagpipes
========

Bagpipes is a resourceful plugin, meaning that it provides a bundled set of resources (ala REST) for a Rails application. In particular, installing Bagpipes 

Example
=======

rake bagpipes:install


Integration
===========
You'll need some sort of authentication scheme that provides the following hooks in the controller:
  logged_in?
  current_user

The easiest way to take care of this is to install the restful authentication plugin.

You'll also need to define a new association in your user (or account or whatever) model, by adding this line:

has_one :member, :as => :user, :dependent => :destroy



